pan class=3D"texhtml"><i>x</i> =3D 5</span>. They can be found via the quad=
ratic formula.</figcaption></figure>
<p>In <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elementary_algebra" title=3D=
"Elementary algebra">elementary algebra</a>, the <b>quadratic formula</b>  =
is a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Closed-form_expression" title=
=3D"Closed-form expression">closed-form expression</a> describing the solut=
ions of a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quadratic_equation" titl=
e=3D"Quadratic equation">quadratic equation</a>. Other ways of solving quad=
ratic equations, such as <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Completin=
g_the_square" title=3D"Completing the square">completing the square</a>, yi=
eld the same solutions.
